text: William Henry Caldecourt (28 September 1802 – 21 June 1857) was an English professional cricketer who played first-class cricket from 1821 to 1844. A medium pace underarm bowler who was mainly associated with Cambridge Town Club and Marylebone Cricket Club (MCC), he made 42 known appearances in first-class matches.CricketArchive. Retrieved on 3 December 2008. He represented the Players in the Gentlemen v Players series and the South in the North v.
